find - locate & filer by condition

find / -name "application.properties"

find / -iname "cfg.yml" = find case sensitive

find / -name "*.log" = find by extensiong

find / -mmin -60 = find file modified in last 1 hour

find / -type f -size +100m = find file larger than 100mb

find files and delet them how?
   find /tmp -name "*.tmp" -exec rm{} \;
  or
  find /tmp -name "*.tmp" -delete

find file and run command on it?
  find . -name "*.sh" -exec chmod +x {} \;

hwo do you search for an error insdie log files?
  tail -f application.log | grep -i exception

how do you locate config file on linux?
  find / -name "app.prop"
or
  find /opt/app/cfg -type f -name "*.yml"

how will you view only error lines from log ignoring info message?

tail -f app.log | grep -i error

| pipeout to the next symbol

grep -i error app.log | grep -iv "Info"
  -v remove lines contaiing info



